239
00:17:08,590 --> 00:17:17,940
God. And God is interested in prayer, and so shall we. Therefore, prayer undergirds this ministry

240
00:17:17,940 --> 00:17:29,660
and will be a core value as we go into the future. Number five in our list. Again, not in importance,

241
00:17:29,660 --> 00:17:36,920
but just in our list, we value Scripture. Scripture will be a key value. The Bible says

242
00:17:36,920 --> 00:17:41,000
in 2 Timothy 3.16, all Scripture is inspired by God

243
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:45,100
and is useful for teaching the truth, rebuking

244
00:17:45,100 --> 00:17:48,910
error, correcting faults, and giving

245
00:17:48,910 --> 00:17:53,210
instruction for right living, so that the person who serves God

246
00:17:53,210 --> 00:17:57,050
may be fully qualified and equipped to do every

247
00:17:57,050 --> 00:18:02,140
kind of good deed. That's what Scripture does

248
00:18:02,140 --> 00:18:06,930
for us. We're a church that has always been founded on

249
00:18:06,930 --> 00:18:08,910
Scripture, preaching Scripture, living

250
00:18:08,910 --> 00:18:10,670
Scripture. We're going to be a

251
00:18:10,670 --> 00:18:12,950
church that continues to value deeply

252
00:18:12,950 --> 00:18:14,990
the Scriptures and the application

253
00:18:14,990 --> 00:18:16,930
of those Scriptures in

254
00:18:16,930 --> 00:18:17,970
our daily lives.

255
00:18:19,310 --> 00:18:21,370
And I believe that when we bring Scripture

256
00:18:21,370 --> 00:18:23,530
to bear upon the very issues

257
00:18:23,530 --> 00:18:24,430
of our souls,

258
00:18:26,300 --> 00:18:28,360
that God matures us therefore in Christ

259
00:18:28,360 --> 00:18:30,420
and prepares us

260
00:18:30,420 --> 00:18:31,700
for service in the Kingdom.

261
00:18:32,740 --> 00:18:34,600
That will be our heart, to take in

262
00:18:34,600 --> 00:18:36,680
Scripture, to apply it,

263
00:18:36,860 --> 00:18:39,440
to live it, and

264
00:18:39,440 --> 00:18:42,880
Therefore, let God be blessed as we serve faithfully and with maturity.

265
00:18:43,970 --> 00:18:45,270
So we're going to value Scripture.

266
00:18:48,600 --> 00:18:50,780
We will value authentic community.

267
00:18:53,360 --> 00:18:55,000
Churches have community.

268
00:18:55,580 --> 00:18:58,540
Every gathering has some kind of community.

269
00:18:59,220 --> 00:19:01,520
There are relationships within a group of people.

270
00:19:02,560 --> 00:19:05,200
The question is, is it authentic?

271
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:06,440
Is it real?

272
00:19:06,440 --> 00:19:12,180
Or is it what some have termed pseudo-community, kind of pretend community?

273
00:19:12,820 --> 00:19:18,140
We want to be a place where we are really known by God and each other

274
00:19:18,140 --> 00:19:22,590
and are in a process of being matured in Christ

275
00:19:22,590 --> 00:19:25,530
whereby we need each other in the journey.

276
00:19:27,020 --> 00:19:29,080
And to do that, we have to know each other.

277
00:19:30,080 --> 00:19:31,640
You know why that's so frightening to me?

278
00:19:32,960 --> 00:19:34,860
Because I'm so darn self-protective.

279
00:19:37,400 --> 00:19:39,100
And so this one speaks to me.

280
00:19:40,860 --> 00:19:42,280
You know, we're all self-protective.

281
00:19:42,280 --> 00:19:49,700
and actually we can't love truly and authentically from behind our walls.

282
00:19:49,820 --> 00:19:50,840
We're going to have to be known.

283
00:19:52,180 --> 00:19:55,380
I'm in a crown study right now studying total life stewardship

284
00:19:55,380 --> 00:19:58,900
and it's so tricky sometimes because I want to be the pastor

285
00:19:58,900 --> 00:20:03,840
and have it all together and try and be cool and collected

286
00:20:03,840 --> 00:20:06,540
and yes, my subjects, that kind of mentality.

287
00:20:06,580 --> 00:20:07,320
And that's terrible.

288
00:20:08,290 --> 00:20:14,010
I've got to be in that group loving them and having them love me in all of my junk.

289
00:20:16,290 --> 00:20:18,310
It's hard sometimes to let them peer into the,

290
00:20:18,390 --> 00:20:21,110
what if they really see me for who I am?

291
00:20:23,320 --> 00:20:24,320
It's threatening for me.

292
00:20:25,480 --> 00:20:26,680
It's threatening for all of us.

293
00:20:27,940 --> 00:20:29,820
But I believe as we really live

294
00:20:29,820 --> 00:20:32,000
and authentically allow ourselves

295
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:34,640
to be known by Christ and by each other,

296
00:20:34,940 --> 00:20:36,460
then we can love each other,

297
00:20:36,460 --> 00:20:39,160
then we can strengthen and mature each other

298
00:20:39,160 --> 00:20:41,420
instead of staying behind our walls.

299
00:20:43,650 --> 00:20:44,810
It's a great challenge for me.

300
00:20:45,780 --> 00:20:46,540
Pray for me.

301
00:20:47,280 --> 00:20:48,660
Because if the church is going to be

302
00:20:48,660 --> 00:20:49,900
about authentic community,

303
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:53,020
For crying out loud, the pastor better live it as well.

304
00:20:53,080 --> 00:20:53,260
Amen?

305
00:20:54,580 --> 00:20:54,940
Amen.

306
00:20:56,080 --> 00:20:57,080
So help me, Jesus.

307
00:21:00,520 --> 00:21:02,340
But here's Community Acts chapter 2.

308
00:21:03,510 --> 00:21:09,200
And all the believers met together constantly and shared everything they had.

309
00:21:10,200 --> 00:21:13,800
They sold their possessions and shared the proceeds with those in need.

310
00:21:14,100 --> 00:21:18,240
They worshiped together at the temple each day, met in homes for the Lord's Supper,

311
00:21:18,440 --> 00:21:21,820
and shared their meals with great joy and generosity.

312
00:21:21,820 --> 00:21:25,500
and all the while praising God

313
00:21:25,500 --> 00:21:28,120
and enjoying the goodwill of all the people.

314
00:21:29,740 --> 00:21:31,720
And each day the Lord added to their group

315
00:21:31,720 --> 00:21:33,080
those who were being saved.

316
00:21:34,500 --> 00:21:35,260
There's our model.

317
00:21:36,450 --> 00:21:37,930
Can we be the kind of church

318
00:21:37,930 --> 00:21:40,410
that is living and meeting in homes

319
00:21:40,410 --> 00:21:41,650
and gathering together

320
00:21:41,650 --> 00:21:43,990
and enjoying each other's presence and fellowship

321
00:21:43,990 --> 00:21:46,130
so richly and so deeply

322
00:21:46,130 --> 00:21:49,410
that people say God is in their midst

323
00:21:49,410 --> 00:21:53,140
and God brings people to be saved on a daily basis.

324
00:21:53,140 --> 00:21:58,350
And that requires we get past all of our, I'm fine, how are you?

325
00:21:58,470 --> 00:22:02,150
Fine, fine, great, praise the Lord, fine, fine, everybody's so fine.

326
00:22:03,220 --> 00:22:04,280
But we're not.

327
00:22:05,740 --> 00:22:08,180
We all need each other.

328
00:22:08,920 --> 00:22:11,220
And we all need Jesus.

329
00:22:11,700 --> 00:22:16,980
And somewhere we have to be authentic enough to admit what's really going on.

330
00:22:19,630 --> 00:22:21,870
So we'll be a church of authentic community.

331
00:22:24,910 --> 00:22:28,300
Scares me to death, but it's got to be.

332
00:22:28,300 --> 00:22:36,970
Number seven, we're going to be a church that values high participation.

333
00:22:39,520 --> 00:22:45,440
High participation is the antithesis of just sitting and soaking.

334
00:22:45,960 --> 00:22:51,180
High participation says that we believe that all of us in Christ,

335
00:22:52,260 --> 00:22:55,620
not just some of us, not just 20% of us,

336
00:22:56,200 --> 00:23:00,380
all of us are called to maturity and to service,

337
00:23:00,380 --> 00:23:02,320
using their spiritual gifts

338
00:23:02,320 --> 00:23:04,620
and participating in the ministry

339
00:23:04,620 --> 00:23:06,460
that God has for us.

340
00:23:08,400 --> 00:23:11,580
We believe that if you are a follower of Jesus Christ,

341
00:23:12,540 --> 00:23:14,500
then you will be active on that journey

342
00:23:14,500 --> 00:23:15,540
towards maturity.

343
00:23:15,920 --> 00:23:17,580
That you'll be active as a servant

344
00:23:17,580 --> 00:23:19,140
in the kingdom of God.

345
00:23:21,280 --> 00:23:23,520
It's not an option just to come

346
00:23:23,520 --> 00:23:25,280
and kick back

347
00:23:25,280 --> 00:23:27,390
and just soak it up.

348
00:23:27,610 --> 00:23:30,210
There are seasons, friends, for that experience.

349
00:23:30,410 --> 00:23:32,250
There are times to sit and soak.

350
00:23:32,250 --> 00:23:40,840
but that's not the norm. That's a healing time, and sometimes we all need that, but as a rule of

351
00:23:40,840 --> 00:23:50,260
practice, we are to be involved, participating, and letting God use us in His ministry, and so we're

352
00:23:50,260 --> 00:23:58,040
going to value high participation and encourage all of us to be involved in the kingdom. That's

353
00:23:58,040 --> 00:24:08,740
high participation. That's threatening too because it cuts up against a lot of models of church that

354
00:24:08,740 --> 00:24:14,200
Let's say you come, you receive, you go home, and you rate the pastor how good was the service.

355
00:24:14,820 --> 00:24:17,500
Good, marginal, not so good that day.

356
00:24:19,650 --> 00:24:20,750
I'm not going to be about that.

357
00:24:21,130 --> 00:24:22,410
You can still rate my sermons.

358
00:24:22,490 --> 00:24:23,010
That's okay.

359
00:24:24,020 --> 00:24:24,940
Just don't tell anybody.

360
00:24:25,880 --> 00:24:26,480
I'm just kidding.

361
00:24:28,560 --> 00:24:32,740
But really, it's not about coming and just receiving and going home and that's it.

362
00:24:33,060 --> 00:24:39,860
The kingdom is living for Christ that others may see him, come to know him through us.

363
00:24:41,480 --> 00:24:42,900
We're going to be a church of high participation.

364
00:24:43,560 --> 00:24:48,150
We're going to be, number eight, a church that is culturally relevant.

365
00:24:50,520 --> 00:24:55,950
We take our cue from Jesus because Jesus is the ultimate missionary.

366
00:24:56,570 --> 00:25:02,950
Jesus was so culturally relevant to us that he became one of us.

367
00:25:04,860 --> 00:25:10,500
That's about as radical and accommodating as you can get to share the message.

368
00:25:11,300 --> 00:25:12,360
He became one of us.

369
00:25:13,720 --> 00:25:16,380
We take our cue from Paul, the great missionary,

370
00:25:16,680 --> 00:25:18,480
who said in 1 Corinthians 9,

371
00:25:18,980 --> 00:25:21,000
when I am with those who are oppressed,

372
00:25:21,900 --> 00:25:25,680
I share their oppression so that I might bring them to Christ.

373
00:25:26,810 --> 00:25:30,990
Yes, I try to find common ground with everyone

374
00:25:30,990 --> 00:25:33,910
so that I might bring them to Christ.

375
00:25:34,550 --> 00:25:36,090
Finding the common ground,

376
00:25:36,490 --> 00:25:38,610
connecting in a language they understand,

377
00:25:39,610 --> 00:25:42,890
ministering in context where people really live,

378
00:25:43,130 --> 00:25:44,670
That's culturally relevant.

379
00:25:45,310 --> 00:25:49,390
Doctrinally pure, of course, but relevant in the world today.

380
00:25:52,050 --> 00:25:54,570
And, of course, that always brings us to a critical challenge.

381
00:25:54,970 --> 00:25:59,330
How do you be culturally relevant without accommodating to the values of the world

382
00:25:59,330 --> 00:26:05,170
that we don't become like the world, but use the world to communicate?

383
00:26:05,970 --> 00:26:09,570
And a critical engagement of those issues is the constant process

384
00:26:09,570 --> 00:26:12,550
of a church trying to be culturally relevant.

385
00:26:12,550 --> 00:26:16,890
It's the critical process that every missionary goes through when they get to the foreign land.

386
00:26:17,230 --> 00:26:21,350
They figure out what in their culture, what in the language, what in the foods,

387
00:26:21,690 --> 00:26:25,250
what in everything can they use to communicate Jesus

388
00:26:25,250 --> 00:26:29,540
without being co-opted by the negative parts of that culture.

389
00:26:31,070 --> 00:26:32,390
It's a missional challenge.

390
00:26:32,930 --> 00:26:34,210
It's a critical evaluation.

391
00:26:34,890 --> 00:26:38,810
It requires much thought and prayer, but it must be done.

392
00:26:38,810 --> 00:26:42,060
and we will be involved in critical engagement

393
00:26:42,060 --> 00:26:44,560
that we might share the message,

394
00:26:44,700 --> 00:26:46,080
that people might hear it,

395
00:26:47,020 --> 00:26:48,140
understand it,

396
00:26:48,140 --> 00:26:50,500
and be able to make that choice

397
00:26:50,500 --> 00:26:52,580
to follow Jesus.

398
00:26:55,790 --> 00:26:58,410
The last value that we came up with on that retreat

399
00:26:58,410 --> 00:27:00,370
and have been processing ever since

400
00:27:00,370 --> 00:27:03,150
is that we value ministry

401
00:27:03,150 --> 00:27:05,410
by the power of the Holy Spirit.

402
00:27:07,120 --> 00:27:10,660
We recognize that without the Holy Spirit's power

403
00:27:10,660 --> 00:27:12,100
flowing through us,

404
00:27:12,100 --> 00:27:17,360
Our ministries will be totally bereft of any strength or impact.

405
00:27:18,020 --> 00:27:21,140
We'll just be going through the motions.

406
00:27:23,040 --> 00:27:26,300
And we don't want to be a church that just goes through the motions.

407
00:27:26,680 --> 00:27:30,980
We want to be a church that does ministry in the power of the Holy Spirit.

408
00:27:33,720 --> 00:27:40,370
Jesus said, my authority, take this message of repentance to all the nations.

409
00:27:40,370 --> 00:27:42,450
beginning in Jerusalem.

410
00:27:43,550 --> 00:27:45,870
There is forgiveness of sins, says Jesus,

411
00:27:46,010 --> 00:27:47,530
for all who turn to me.

412
00:27:48,190 --> 00:27:50,770
You are witnesses of all these things.

413
00:27:51,570 --> 00:27:53,650
And now I will send the Holy Spirit

414
00:27:53,650 --> 00:27:55,490
just as my Father promised.

415
00:27:56,210 --> 00:27:57,510
But stay here in the city

416
00:27:57,510 --> 00:27:59,210
until the Holy Spirit comes

417
00:27:59,210 --> 00:28:01,970
and fills you with power from heaven.

418
00:28:03,080 --> 00:28:04,660
Don't attempt ministry

419
00:28:04,660 --> 00:28:07,720
unless you're filled with the power, says Jesus.

420
00:28:08,500 --> 00:28:10,040
And the same is true with us.

421
00:28:11,010 --> 00:28:15,890
So we're going to be a church that values always invoking the power of the Holy Spirit

422
00:28:15,890 --> 00:28:18,310
in everything we do in ministry.

423
00:28:19,590 --> 00:28:20,290
It's a value.

424
00:28:21,800 --> 00:28:24,180
We look forward to seeing how God will play that out with us.

425
00:28:26,190 --> 00:28:27,130
That's the mission.

426
00:28:27,710 --> 00:28:29,010
Those are the values.

427
00:28:30,620 --> 00:28:36,380
What does it look like, though, to do all of that here in North Orange County?

428
00:28:38,440 --> 00:28:40,220
That's the vision question.

429
00:28:41,200 --> 00:28:42,720
Mission is non-negotiable.

430
00:28:42,720 --> 00:28:44,360
Mission has always been.

431
00:28:44,360 --> 00:28:46,960
and mission is the biblical model of the church.

432
00:28:47,220 --> 00:28:52,960
The vision is, what does that look like right here in 2003?

433
00:28:55,690 --> 00:28:58,910
And vision shifts continuously.

434
00:29:01,090 --> 00:29:05,970
And as the culture and the world and the community changes every few years,

435
00:29:05,970 --> 00:29:08,530
the mission may change that fast

436
00:29:08,530 --> 00:29:13,780
if we're going to be missional people that live out the vision in the community.

437
00:29:15,740 --> 00:29:19,160
We've done some things to try and understand our community

438
00:29:19,160 --> 00:29:21,300
and God's vision for this church.

439
00:29:22,790 --> 00:29:24,470
We've been studying this community.

440
00:29:26,010 --> 00:29:28,790
And we had a study done from the Percept group recently

441
00:29:28,790 --> 00:29:31,670
that maps out the demographics, the ethnographics,

442
00:29:32,090 --> 00:29:36,150
the spiritual receptivity and involvement of this community.

443
00:29:36,570 --> 00:29:41,990
And we decided to look at a 10-mile radius from this church building.

444
00:29:43,990 --> 00:29:47,370
And so a radius was drawn, and a radius has been studied.

445
00:29:48,560 --> 00:29:51,240
And we've got an entire booklet, and we can make copies of that

446
00:29:51,240 --> 00:29:56,180
If you'd like to see that, here are some salient issues that come out of that study.

447
00:29:57,450 --> 00:30:00,670
We have discovered in a 10-mile radius of this church

448
00:30:00,670 --> 00:30:05,070
that we are in an increasingly diverse ethnic community.

449
00:30:06,120 --> 00:30:07,020
You knew that.

450
00:30:08,280 --> 00:30:12,940
But what's interesting to see is exactly what kinds of folks are here in that community.

451
00:30:14,980 --> 00:30:19,520
We are in a community of educated and established affluent families

452
00:30:19,520 --> 00:30:23,260
and young and coming families, higher than the national average,

453
00:30:23,320 --> 00:30:28,320
by quite a bit in those two categories in a 10-mile radius of this church.

454
00:30:29,720 --> 00:30:34,120
We note that this community is increasingly becoming younger and younger.

455
00:30:35,970 --> 00:30:41,450
We discern from this study that the community dislikes all contacts,

456
00:30:42,310 --> 00:30:47,630
including advertising, mailing, and most vehemently, face-to-face.

457
00:30:49,240 --> 00:30:50,000
They don't want it.

458
00:30:52,160 --> 00:30:55,500
It's tough to share the gospel when they don't want to get it in the mail,

459
00:30:55,500 --> 00:31:07,210
by phone or knock knock here we are they want to cocoon hide they've got challenges there

460
00:31:07,210 --> 00:31:14,210
our community prefers if they were to come to church an intellectually challenging worship

461
00:31:14,210 --> 00:31:23,400
style challenge for us most saddening to me was this and yet that gives me the most power and

462
00:31:23,400 --> 00:31:30,520
purpose for the church is that from this study the best estimate they have is that half of the

463
00:31:30,520 --> 00:31:43,210
people in this 10-mile radius have no faith involvement whatsoever. None. Totally lost.

464
00:31:44,780 --> 00:31:53,840
Totally without hope. Totally without purpose. Totally without direction. Totally just sheep

465
00:31:53,840 --> 00:32:05,910
on a hillside, lost with no shepherd, no God, no faith involvement whatsoever. And our church

466
00:32:05,910 --> 00:32:12,130
sits in the middle of thousands and thousands of people

467
00:32:12,130 --> 00:32:18,700
that are lost and going to hell with no hope

468
00:32:18,700 --> 00:32:23,910
unless we radiate Jesus from this

469
00:32:23,910 --> 00:32:29,980
focal point to these people. Our mission

470
00:32:29,980 --> 00:32:34,850
field is right outside the door. The moment

471
00:32:34,850 --> 00:32:38,670
you step into your car, you drive one block, you've just entered the

472
00:32:38,670 --> 00:32:45,160
mission zone. Yes, we must do ministry around the globe

473
00:32:45,160 --> 00:32:47,780
because there is a need for missions everywhere.

474
00:32:47,780 --> 00:32:55,140
But missions is now as close to this door as it ever has been.

475
00:32:57,610 --> 00:32:59,510
And friends, now that we live in Los Angeles,

476
00:32:59,650 --> 00:33:02,870
a megalopolis that exports culture around the world,

477
00:33:03,070 --> 00:33:05,130
and everybody wants to be here,

478
00:33:05,590 --> 00:33:09,170
this is, in some ways, the center of the world.

479
00:33:10,830 --> 00:33:14,450
If you think about it, technologically, culturally, socially,

480
00:33:14,570 --> 00:33:18,470
what happens in L.A. will end up everywhere else eventually.

481
00:33:18,470 --> 00:33:23,580
we are at the very center of what's happening in many ways around the world.

482
00:33:25,270 --> 00:33:31,550
How we preach Christ and affect lives will have a worldwide impact from this place.

483
00:33:35,230 --> 00:33:37,810
The opportunities are humongous.

484
00:33:39,720 --> 00:33:42,200
We must rise and take the challenge.

485
00:33:42,980 --> 00:33:45,680
Couple these things with the mission field being at our door,

486
00:33:45,820 --> 00:33:49,200
with this reality that as Henry Blackaby taught us in Experiencing God,

487
00:33:49,200 --> 00:33:58,100
your job he says as a servant is to follow jesus example do what the father is already doing

488
00:33:58,100 --> 00:34:08,360
watch to see where god is at work and then join him and so we've been looking and studying god

489
00:34:08,360 --> 00:34:16,800
what are you doing in our midst what is new where what are you seeming to bless and we see that god

490
00:34:16,800 --> 00:34:21,360
is bringing a variety of people of all ages to this church but he is particularly bringing a lot

491
00:34:21,360 --> 00:34:28,080
of young families, and I believe that once they are one to Christ and matured, they are the future

492
00:34:28,080 --> 00:34:35,250
of this church and the church at large. That's why we need a families and children's pastor to

493
00:34:35,250 --> 00:34:41,080
really begin to move in that area that God is bringing, and I believe that once we reach them

494
00:34:41,080 --> 00:34:46,360
for Christ, we'll plug them into the mission of this church to worship, to outreach, to experience

495
00:34:46,360 --> 00:34:53,640
authentic community, to engage in discipleship and maturity, and to serve in ministry. We want

496
00:34:53,640 --> 00:35:00,250
to see evangelism in all the ages and programs for families and children and small groups and

497
00:35:00,250 --> 00:35:07,190
affinity groups and to accomplish that vision we need everyone in this church to be involved

498
00:35:07,190 --> 00:35:14,980
everyone and now i want you to hear me very clearly because i mean this from the bottom

499
00:35:14,980 --> 00:35:27,060
of my self-protective heart and i mean this we need our mature seniors to be the mentors

500
00:35:27,060 --> 00:35:31,140
and the prayer warriors and the leaders on this journey

501
00:35:31,140 --> 00:35:33,700
that families would follow.

502
00:35:35,320 --> 00:35:38,540
Because my generation, friends, let me share again

503
00:35:38,540 --> 00:35:40,640
from something deep that burdens me greatly.

504
00:35:42,520 --> 00:35:44,300
I'm 37 years old this month.

505
00:35:45,420 --> 00:35:48,320
I'm the bleeding edge of what they call Generation X,

506
00:35:49,490 --> 00:35:51,450
the boom behind the baby boom.

507
00:35:53,090 --> 00:35:56,090
And as much has been written about the generation of the boomers

508
00:35:56,090 --> 00:35:59,450
and all of that, this next generation also is a puzzle

509
00:35:59,450 --> 00:36:04,180
because here's a generation that has been raised in homes

510
00:36:04,180 --> 00:36:08,990
where there were no Bibles, no Christ, no church.

511
00:36:08,990 --> 00:36:10,770
In fact, no mom and dad.

512
00:36:12,030 --> 00:36:15,950
The fact that my parents are married and both love Jesus

513
00:36:15,950 --> 00:36:20,040
makes me the anomaly, not the norm.

514
00:36:21,730 --> 00:36:22,550
And that is sad.

515
00:36:24,080 --> 00:36:26,220
And when I talk about my family with friends,

516
00:36:26,340 --> 00:36:28,700
they don't relate because my parents are still together

517
00:36:28,700 --> 00:36:30,040
and my parents love Jesus.

518
00:36:30,460 --> 00:36:32,300
And that puts me way out there.

519
00:36:32,520 --> 00:36:38,220
My generation was raised by latchkey experience,

520
00:36:38,500 --> 00:36:41,100
raised on television from 3 to 6 o'clock,

521
00:36:41,980 --> 00:36:46,740
raised on the values of the world coming through the tube for 3 to 4 hours a day,

522
00:36:48,990 --> 00:36:52,210
and then seeing that everybody who commits to them eventually leaves them

523
00:36:52,210 --> 00:36:54,070
and divorces and moves on.

524
00:36:54,740 --> 00:36:59,940
Or pursues the good life, the education, the BMWs and the Lexuses

525
00:36:59,940 --> 00:37:03,200
and all of those things at the risk of their own children.

526
00:37:03,340 --> 00:37:04,280
That's my generation.

527
00:37:05,570 --> 00:37:08,190
And they are a walking, wounded generation.

528
00:37:08,430 --> 00:37:10,230
They are an addicted generation.

529
00:37:10,550 --> 00:37:13,070
And they are now coming into their own,

530
00:37:13,390 --> 00:37:15,970
raising their own children for the first time.

531
00:37:17,860 --> 00:37:19,280
And they don't know what to do.

532
00:37:20,210 --> 00:37:24,630
But they know they don't want to do what happened to them.

533
00:37:26,460 --> 00:37:29,620
They know they don't want to repeat that cycle.

534
00:37:29,940 --> 00:37:34,450
But they are bereft of any spirituality that is meaningful.

535
00:37:34,450 --> 00:37:37,810
They are lost and they need mentoring.

536
00:37:38,830 --> 00:37:42,610
They need you folks to pull them into their lives,

537
00:37:42,750 --> 00:37:43,690
into your lives,

538
00:37:44,010 --> 00:37:47,090
and just model family,

539
00:37:48,210 --> 00:37:49,030
model Jesus,

540
00:37:49,850 --> 00:37:50,670
model prayer,

541
00:37:51,130 --> 00:37:52,110
model laughter,

542
00:37:52,550 --> 00:37:53,590
model goodness,

543
00:37:53,990 --> 00:37:54,950
model hope,

544
00:37:55,310 --> 00:37:57,330
model everything that they have missed.

545
00:37:59,820 --> 00:38:01,100
And I hurt for my generation.

546
00:38:02,310 --> 00:38:04,030
Because if they're not one to Christ,

547
00:38:04,030 --> 00:38:08,770
they will go through their lives completely devoid of Jesus.

548
00:38:10,660 --> 00:38:12,080
And that's bad for the church.

549
00:38:12,240 --> 00:38:13,440
It's bad for our country.

550
00:38:14,310 --> 00:38:16,030
It's bad for the kingdom of God.

551
00:38:19,050 --> 00:38:22,030
And for various reasons, God is beginning to bring this generation

552
00:38:22,030 --> 00:38:24,970
and their little children and their babies and filling up our nursery.

553
00:38:25,370 --> 00:38:29,310
But they need you to love them and to mentor them.

554
00:38:29,510 --> 00:38:33,450
And it's one of my hopes to see our primetime ministries begin a training zone

555
00:38:33,450 --> 00:38:36,390
for faithful disciples and mentors

556
00:38:36,390 --> 00:38:38,670
that can bring in these people

557
00:38:38,670 --> 00:38:41,560
and really love them.

558
00:38:43,090 --> 00:38:43,670
And you know what?

559
00:38:43,690 --> 00:38:44,890
I need some of that love too.

560
00:38:46,630 --> 00:38:47,850
Don't count me out as well.

561
00:38:49,400 --> 00:38:50,280
I can use it as well.

562
00:38:53,190 --> 00:38:54,310
When we're mature in Christ,

563
00:38:54,450 --> 00:38:56,130
our food is to do the will of God.

564
00:38:56,250 --> 00:38:57,570
It's to give ourselves away.

565
00:38:57,650 --> 00:38:58,570
It's to bless others.

566
00:38:59,590 --> 00:39:00,830
That's how we get filled up.

567
00:39:00,870 --> 00:39:02,390
And I really believe, my friends

568
00:39:02,390 --> 00:39:03,970
and my mature ones in Christ,

569
00:39:03,970 --> 00:39:06,470
that as you begin to give

570
00:39:06,470 --> 00:39:07,530
to the next generation

571
00:39:07,530 --> 00:39:08,870
and pour into them

572
00:39:08,870 --> 00:39:12,150
and share your life, your experiences with Christ.

573
00:39:12,150 --> 00:39:16,970
It will fill you up in ways that I cannot even begin to describe.

574
00:39:18,950 --> 00:39:22,850
But it's scary because it involves us being in authentic community.

575
00:39:24,800 --> 00:39:26,080
That's frightening for everybody.

576
00:39:28,030 --> 00:39:30,130
My generation is craving community.

577
00:39:30,290 --> 00:39:34,910
That's why they go to Starbucks and spend $3 a day on Frappuccino Latte with a twist

578
00:39:34,910 --> 00:39:37,120
and spend hours.

579
00:39:37,620 --> 00:39:39,700
You know what Starbucks' model is?

580
00:39:39,700 --> 00:39:42,600
their marketing slogan is

581
00:39:42,600 --> 00:39:44,360
they want to be the third place.

582
00:39:46,410 --> 00:39:48,930
Home, work, and Starbucks.

583
00:39:50,490 --> 00:39:53,810
They want you to spend your third time,

584
00:39:53,930 --> 00:39:55,770
your third place in their place.

585
00:39:56,030 --> 00:39:56,670
And you know what?

586
00:39:56,870 --> 00:39:59,050
My generation just eats that up.

587
00:39:59,580 --> 00:40:01,520
Because they're looking for community.

588
00:40:01,900 --> 00:40:03,600
They're looking for a place to be

589
00:40:03,600 --> 00:40:06,040
where they can be known.

590
00:40:06,180 --> 00:40:08,500
But they're frightened to death at the same time.

591
00:40:08,760 --> 00:40:09,360
They talk.

592
00:40:09,540 --> 00:40:10,660
They have pseudo-community.

593
00:40:10,660 --> 00:40:12,260
They want to really engage.

594
00:40:12,360 --> 00:40:13,700
but they're also frightened to death

595
00:40:13,700 --> 00:40:14,840
because if you love them,

596
00:40:15,080 --> 00:40:16,720
everybody who loves them leaves them.

597
00:40:18,220 --> 00:40:20,280
Church, we've got to love them

598
00:40:20,280 --> 00:40:21,120
and never leave them

599
00:40:21,120 --> 00:40:26,350
and show them what it means to commit

600
00:40:26,350 --> 00:40:29,610
and love them through their pain

601
00:40:29,610 --> 00:40:31,750
and point them to Jesus

602
00:40:31,750 --> 00:40:36,140
because then they'll rise up

603
00:40:36,140 --> 00:40:37,540
and be the next wave of leadership

604
00:40:37,540 --> 00:40:38,720
that'll take this church

605
00:40:38,720 --> 00:40:40,640
to the next 50, the next 100 years.

606
00:40:42,300 --> 00:40:43,500
God is bringing them

607
00:40:43,500 --> 00:40:45,880
and we've got to figure out

608
00:40:45,880 --> 00:40:48,180
how to really engage and love

609
00:40:48,180 --> 00:40:49,320
and I need you all.

610
00:40:49,320 --> 00:40:51,000
I need this service predominantly.

611
00:40:51,520 --> 00:40:52,240
I need you.

612
00:40:52,360 --> 00:40:53,120
The board needs you.

613
00:40:53,220 --> 00:40:54,260
The church needs you

614
00:40:54,260 --> 00:40:58,180
to be that kind of loving, mentoring,

615
00:40:59,210 --> 00:41:01,130
godly discipleship kind of leaders

616
00:41:01,130 --> 00:41:05,850
that love this next generation.

617
00:41:06,150 --> 00:41:07,130
And they are prickly.

618
00:41:08,350 --> 00:41:09,490
Their hairdos are funny.

619
00:41:12,960 --> 00:41:13,900
They're messed up

620
00:41:13,900 --> 00:41:17,910
because they were sinned against.

621
00:41:23,220 --> 00:41:23,860
And they need you.

622
00:41:24,930 --> 00:41:27,090
And I need you to be there for them.

623
00:41:29,440 --> 00:41:30,500
One of the riches of our church

624
00:41:30,500 --> 00:41:32,100
is our multi-generational ministry.

625
00:41:32,100 --> 00:41:35,070
and we are all, all needed

626
00:41:35,070 --> 00:41:37,540
to see God's will accomplished.

627
00:41:38,830 --> 00:41:40,010
And so my challenge is

628
00:41:40,010 --> 00:41:42,270
will you join God in what He is doing?

629
00:41:44,260 --> 00:41:46,580
And will we listen to what God is doing

630
00:41:46,580 --> 00:41:49,400
and be a part of what God is doing?

631
00:41:51,980 --> 00:41:53,860
Here are some things that God is doing

632
00:41:53,860 --> 00:41:54,760
to encourage you.

633
00:41:58,360 --> 00:41:59,620
We've been doing Owning the Vision

634
00:41:59,620 --> 00:42:01,600
because we're going to own this place

635
00:42:01,600 --> 00:42:02,700
back from the bank

636
00:42:02,700 --> 00:42:04,220
and we're going to own this vision,

637
00:42:04,900 --> 00:42:05,620
this mission,

638
00:42:06,100 --> 00:42:08,640
these values in the life of this church.

639
00:42:08,700 --> 00:42:13,790
And here is what you have pledged as a church over the next three years

640
00:42:13,790 --> 00:42:16,610
in terms of paying down our debt and obligations

641
00:42:16,610 --> 00:42:22,010
and paying off these facilities as a gift to the future generations.

642
00:42:22,670 --> 00:42:24,870
That's why we're going to attack it so hard,

643
00:42:24,890 --> 00:42:27,670
because it's a gift to the next generations.

644
00:42:29,620 --> 00:42:37,090
You have pledged in this next three-year cycle $772,407.

645
00:42:38,090 --> 00:42:41,210
Praise the Lord. Praise the Lord.

646
00:42:41,290 --> 00:42:51,250
And I thank you from the bottom of my self-protective heart for your commitment and your stewardship and your sacrifice.

647
00:42:53,000 --> 00:42:55,740
It will not be for naught.

648
00:42:56,380 --> 00:42:57,740
It will not be in vain.

649
00:42:59,400 --> 00:42:59,960
Bless you.

650
00:43:01,650 --> 00:43:05,490
For those who still want to get on board, you are more than welcome to join into all this.

651
00:43:05,810 --> 00:43:09,850
And every year as we move into this, we're going to invite the new families that have come to get involved.

652
00:43:09,850 --> 00:43:14,550
And I still want us to see us pay off a million by the time three years is done.

653
00:43:15,800 --> 00:43:20,340
But thank you for your commitment of $772,407.

654
00:43:22,170 --> 00:43:23,350
I bless you.

655
00:43:23,690 --> 00:43:24,290
I thank you.

656
